## 3. Target Audience & Searcher Profile

**Who is searching this keyword:** First-time renters (students, recent graduates, young professionals), immigrants or newcomers to the United States who have not yet established a U.S. credit file, and renters who have experienced financial hardship and are rebuilding. This audience skews toward the 18-32 age range and includes gig workers and freelancers whose income is documented but unconventional.

**Stage of the renter journey:** Decision and transaction. These searchers are not browsing broadly. They have a specific housing need, often with a timeline, and are trying to determine whether they can qualify for an apartment and what they need to do to get one.

**Problem they are trying to solve:** They have encountered a credit check requirement (or anticipate one) and are not confident their credit history will satisfy a landlord. They want to know whether apartments exist that skip the check entirely and, if not, what alternatives will actually get them approved.

**Expected answer format:** Based on the SERP, they expect a structured, practical how-to guide that directly answers the question and gives them actionable steps. They do not want a definition essay or a general financial education piece.

