*Writing instruction:* Address the risk side honestly. A "no credit check" listing that advertises itself prominently is not always a good sign. Cover 4 red flags: (1) landlord requests deposit before you have seen the unit in person, (2) listing photos appear stock or do not match the unit, (3) landlord asks you to wire money, (4) rent is significantly below market without explanation. Then clarify: a legitimate private landlord who skips the credit check will still meet you in person, show the unit, and use a written lease. This section answers the PAA question "How to avoid credit check for apartment?" and also the implied question "Is renting with no credit check safe?"

